        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(imessage): route direct media captions through attachments",
        "body": "## Summary\n- route direct-handle iMessage media sends through chat resolution plus `send-attachment`\n- split captioned iMessage media into attachment delivery followed by a normal text send\n- keep explicit chat media-only attachment routing covered, and add regressions for direct media plus captions\n- clean up temporary outbound handoff copies after the send path finishes\n\nCloses #87597\n\n## Tests\n- `node_modules/.bin/vitest run extensions/imessage/src/send.test.ts --environment node --reporter=dot`\n  - 26 passed\n- `pnpm check:test-types`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions.tsbuildinfo`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- Behavior addressed: direct-handle iMessage media sends now route through `send-attachment`; captioned media sends deliver the attachment first and the caption as a separate normal text send. Temporary handoff copies are removed after the send path finishes.\n- Real environment tested: PR-head local checkout at `c67f998bc5`, macOS Messages/iMessage bot bridge, configured outbound handoff directory, existing direct 1:1 iMessage conversation. All personal identifiers are redacted from this PR.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: sent one media-only PNG to a direct iMessage handle through the PR-head `sendMessageIMessage` path, then sent captioned PNGs to the same direct-handle target through the same path. The harness used `node --import tsx`, recorded the invoked CLI command names, queried bot-visible Messages history, and checked the handoff directory for a uniquely named cleanup-test copy after send completion.\n- Evidence after fix: redacted live output from the PR-head harness:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"calls\": [\"send-attachment\"],\n  \"sentText\": \"OpenClaw PR #87715 cleanup live test\",\n  \"leftovers\": []\n}\n```\n\nRedacted bot-visible history also showed outgoing `image/png` attachment rows with `missing:false`; captioned cases were followed by outgoing text rows containing the caption. The public PR intentionally omits phone numbers, real chat GUIDs, local user paths, and private message IDs.\n- Observed result after fix: media-only direct send delivered a PNG attachment; captioned direct media delivered a PNG attachment followed by the caption text; the temporary handoff copy was removed after the send completed. This is the behavior that failed before the PR when direct-handle/captioned media fell through legacy RPC `send` with `file`.\n- Not tested: group iMessage media delivery and reply-to media delivery were not live-tested in this pass; they are outside the direct-handle/caption bug fixed here and remain covered only by existing automated coverage.",
